{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-exo-md-js","path":"/1g/nsi/2-representation-des-donnees-types-et-valeurs-de-base/5-les-booleens/exo/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"construire-des-tables-de-vérité\" class=\"anchored\">Construire des tables de vérité</h2>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Produisez les tables de vérité pour les opérations suivantes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>NAND</strong> : <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mtext>&nbsp;NAND&nbsp;</mtext><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>Q</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P \\text{ NAND } Q = !(P \\&amp; Q)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8778em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">&nbsp;NAND&nbsp;</span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li><strong>NOR</strong> : <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mtext>&nbsp;NOR&nbsp;</mtext><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>Q</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P \\text{ NOR } Q = !(P | Q)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8778em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">&nbsp;NOR&nbsp;</span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li><strong>XOR</strong> : <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mtext>&nbsp;XOR&nbsp;</mtext><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>Q</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>Q</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P \\text{ XOR } Q = (P \\&amp; !Q) | (!P \\&amp; Q)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8778em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">&nbsp;XOR&nbsp;</span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><p>Produire des tables de vérité pour :</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>Q</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P \\&amp; !Q</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span></span></span></span>\n</p></li>\n<li><p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>Q</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">!P \\&amp; !Q</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span></span></span></span>\n</p></li>\n<li><p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>Q</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">!P | !Q</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span></span></span></span>\n</p></li>\n<li><p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>Q</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P \\&amp; Q \\&amp; R</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span></span></span></span>\n</p></li>\n<li><p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>Q</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">!P \\&amp; !Q \\&amp; !R</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span></span></span></span>\n</p></li>\n<li><p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>Q</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>R</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>Q</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P \\&amp; Q \\&amp; R | P \\&amp; !Q \\&amp; R</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span></span></span></span>\n</p></li>\n</ul></li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"expressions-équivalentes\" class=\"anchored\">Expressions équivalentes</h2>\n<p><strong>Savoir-faire:</strong> Utiliser une table de vérité pour montrer que deux expressions logiques sont équivalentes</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p>Montrer que:</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>Q</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>Q</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\nP | ( !P \\&amp; Q)=P | Q\n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span></span></span></span></span>\n</p></li>\n<li><p>Utiliser une table de vérité pour démontrer la propriété d’absorption de l’algèbre de Boole:</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>P</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\nP | P \\&amp; Q = P\n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span></span>\n</p></li>\n<li><p>Montrer que:</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>Q</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>Q</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>R</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\nP | Q \\&amp; R = (P | Q) \\&amp; (P | R)\n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>\n</p></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"simplifications-dexpressions-booléennes\" class=\"anchored\">Simplifications d’expressions booléennes</h2>\n<p>Utilisez les lois de l’algèbre de Boole <em>(ne les apprenez pas!)</em> pour simplifier ces expressions.</p>\n<div class=\"callout callout-style-default callout-tip callout-captioned\">\n<div class=\"callout-header d-flex align-content-center\">\n<div class=\"callout-icon-container\">\n<i class=\"callout-icon\"></i>\n</div>\n<div class=\"callout-caption-container flex-fill\">\nAstuce\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"callout-body-container callout-body\">\n<p>Utiliser le <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>×</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\times</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">×</span></span></span></span>\npour le «ET» et le <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>+</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">+</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6667em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">+</span></span></span></span>\npour le «OU» pour pouvoir utiliser les règles habituelles de développement et de factorisant de l’algèbre non booléen.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<ol type=\"1\">\n<li><p>Simplifier l’expression:</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>Q</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>Q</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\n(P | Q)\\&amp;(P |  !Q)\n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>\n</p>\n<p>Vérifier votre résultat avec une table de vérité.</p></li>\n<li><p>Démontrer l’expression de <code>XOR</code> utilisée dans l’exercice 1: <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mtext>&nbsp;XOR&nbsp;</mtext><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>Q</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>Q</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P \\text{ XOR } Q = (P \\&amp; !Q)|(!P \\&amp;Q)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8778em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">&nbsp;XOR&nbsp;</span></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>\n:</p>\n<p>Pour cela commencer par remarquer que:</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mtable rowspacing=\"0.25em\" columnalign=\"right left\" columnspacing=\"0em\"><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel=\"0\" displaystyle=\"true\"><mrow><mn>0</mn><mtext>&nbsp;XOR&nbsp;</mtext><mi>Q</mi><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mtd><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel=\"0\" displaystyle=\"true\"><mrow><mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel=\"0\" displaystyle=\"true\"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mtext>&nbsp;XOR&nbsp;</mtext><mi>Q</mi><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mtd><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel=\"0\" displaystyle=\"true\"><mrow><mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>Q</mi></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr></mtable><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\n\\begin{aligned}\n   0\\ \\text{XOR}\\ Q\\ &amp;=\\ Q \\\\\n   1\\ \\text{XOR}\\ Q\\ &amp;=\\  !Q\n\\end{aligned}\n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:3em;vertical-align:-1.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mtable\"><span class=\"col-align-r\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.75em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.91em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mspace\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">XOR</span></span><span class=\"mspace\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mspace\">&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-2.41em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mspace\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">XOR</span></span><span class=\"mspace\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mspace\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.25em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"col-align-l\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.75em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.91em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-2.41em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.25em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>\n</p>\n<p>Vérifier votre résultat avec une table de vérité.</p></li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"recherche-dexpressions-équivalentes-plus-dur\" class=\"anchored\">Recherche d’expressions équivalentes <em>(Plus dur)</em></h2>\n<p>Exprimer sous forme simplifiée les expressions suivantes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>Q</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>R</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>Q</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>S</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(P \\&amp; Q \\&amp; R) | (P \\&amp; Q \\&amp; S)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>\n</p></li>\n<li><p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>Q</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>Q</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>S</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>S</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(!P | Q) \\&amp; (P | Q | S) \\&amp; !S</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span></span></span></span>\n</p></li>\n<li><p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>Q</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>R</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">!</mo><mi>Q</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>R</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∣</mi><mi>P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>Q</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&amp;</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P \\&amp; !Q \\&amp; !R | P \\&amp; !Q \\&amp; R | P \\&amp; Q \\&amp; R</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mclose\">!</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mord\">∣</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Q</span><span class=\"mord\">&amp;</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span></span></span></span>\n</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Vous pouvez vérifier vos résultats en Python en utilisant la bibliothèque <code>sympy</code> qui propose la fonction <code>simplify_logic</code>(Attention la syntaxe utilisée est: ET: <code>&amp;</code>, OU: <code>| et NON:</code>~`).</p>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">sympy</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">symbols</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">sympy.logic</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">simplify_logic</span>\n<span></span>\n<span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">Q</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">R</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">T</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">symbols</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'P Q R S T'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span></span>\n<span class=\"n\">simplify_logic</span><span class=\"p\">((</span><span class=\"o\">~</span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">Q</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">Q</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;~</span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"p\">)</span> <span class=\"c1\"># renvoie Q &amp; !S</span>\n</pre></div>\n<p>La fonction propose deux modes de simplifications:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Produit(ET) de sommes(OU): <code>simplify_logic(expr, 'cnf')</code></li>\n<li>Somme(OU) de produit(ET): <code>simplify_logic(expr, 'dnf')</code></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"highlight\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"n\">expr</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"P&amp;!Q&amp;!R|P&amp;!Q&amp;R|P&amp;Q&amp;R\"</span>\n<span class=\"n\">simplify_logic</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">expr</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'cnf'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>   <span class=\"c1\"># renvoie P &amp; (R | !Q)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">simplify_logic</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">expr</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'dnf'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>   <span class=\"c1\"># renvoie (P &amp; R) | (P &amp; !Q)</span>\n</pre></div>","frontmatter":{"tocHTML":"<ul><li><a href=\"#construire-des-tables-de-vérité\" data-localhref=\"true\">Construire des tables de vérité</a></li><li><a href=\"#expressions-équivalentes\" data-localhref=\"true\">Expressions équivalentes</a></li><li><a href=\"#simplifications-dexpressions-booléennes\" data-localhref=\"true\">Simplifications d’expressions booléennes</a></li><li><a href=\"#recherche-dexpressions-équivalentes-plus-dur\" data-localhref=\"true\">Recherche d’expressions équivalentes <em>(Plus dur)</em></a></li></ul>"},"fields":{"classe":"1g","chapter":"Les booléens","matter":"nsi","nChapter":"5","part":"Représentation des données : types et valeurs de base","nPart":"2","type":"exo"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"1g/nsi/2-representation-des-donnees-types-et-valeurs-de-base/5-les-booleens/exo"}},"staticQueryHashes":["604483588"],"slicesMap":{}}